<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="35" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1374,2037]" box="[151,582,1374,1400]" pageId="6" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,279,1374,1400]" pageId="6" pageNumber="35">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Length: Ψ, body 9.0 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1374,2037]" pageId="6" pageNumber="35">
General color yellowish brown, vertex with three black spots at apex with the median one longish; frons with each lateral half with 
<number box="[464,479,1454,1480]" pageId="6" pageNumber="35" value="5.0">5</number>
carmine transverse bands. Postfemora with long blackish stripes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1374,2037]" pageId="6" pageNumber="35">
Vertex with anterior margin projected, nearly straight in dorsal view; lateral areas distinctly depressed; median carina percurrent, joining together with sublateral carinae anteriorly. Frons with median carina thin and narrow. Fore wings with 
<number box="[509,538,1572,1598]" pageId="6" pageNumber="35" value="16.0">16</number>
apical cells and 
<number box="[746,761,1572,1598]" pageId="6" pageNumber="35" value="7.0">7</number>
subapical cells, the two middle anteapical cells equally long, Cu 
<number box="[252,260,1628,1642]" pageId="6" pageNumber="35" value="1.0">1</number>
bifurcated at caudad of middle of clavus. (After 
<bibRefCitation author="Melichar" box="[832,1014,1612,1638]" pageId="6" pageNumber="44" refString="Melichar, L. (1914) Monographie der Tropiduchinen (Homoptera). Verhandlungen des Naturforschenden Vereins in Brunn, 53, 1 - 145." type="journal article" year="1914">
Melichar, 
<number box="[951,1014,1612,1638]" pageId="6" pageNumber="35" value="1914.0">1914</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<number box="[1025,1071,1612,1638]" pageId="6" pageNumber="35" value="115.0">115</number>
; 
<figureCitation box="[1084,1171,1612,1638]" captionStart="FIGURES 24 – 35" captionStartId="10.[151,269,1838,1862]" captionTargetBox="[237,1320,193,1812]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[201,1370,156,1825]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 24 – 35. Sogana species. 24 – 27. male genitalia (lateral view). 24. S. clara sp. nov. (holotype). 25. S. hopponis Matsumura. 26. S. pseudohopponis sp. nov. (holotype). 27. S. robustocarina sp. nov. (holotype). 28 – 35. anal segment and pygofer (dorsal view); aedeagus (ventral view); gonostylus (dorsal view); gonostylus and pygofer (ventral view). 28 – 31. S. clara sp. nov. (holotype). 32 – 35. S. hopponis Matsumura. Abbreviations: ap = anal apodeme, At = anal tube, CC = corpus connective, Epr = epiproct, G = gonostylus, P = pygofer, Ppr = paraproct, STC = structure tectiform of connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/181361/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="35">
Fig. 
<number box="[1138,1171,1612,1638]" pageId="6" pageNumber="35" value="28.0">28</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1374,2037]" box="[197,382,1654,1680]" pageId="6" pageNumber="35">Male unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="35" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1374,2037]" pageId="6" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,359,1694,1720]" pageId="6" pageNumber="35">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[365,445,1694,1720]" name="Myanmar" pageId="6" pageNumber="35">Burma</collectingCountry>
(Tenasserim), southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[772,842,1694,1720]" name="China" pageId="6" pageNumber="35">China</collectingCountry>
(Zhejiang [Chekiang]) (?), northern 
<collectingCountry box="[1271,1370,1694,1720]" name="Vietnam" pageId="6" pageNumber="35">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
(Hoa Binh) (?).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="36" pageId="6" pageNumber="35" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1374,2037]" pageId="6" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,319,1773,1799]" pageId="6" pageNumber="35">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Melichar" box="[328,519,1773,1799]" pageId="6" pageNumber="44" refString="Melichar, L. (1914) Monographie der Tropiduchinen (Homoptera). Verhandlungen des Naturforschenden Vereins in Brunn, 53, 1 - 145." type="journal article" year="1914">
Melichar (
<number box="[450,511,1773,1799]" pageId="6" pageNumber="35" value="1914.0">1914</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName box="[649,772,1774,1799]" genus="Logana" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="6" pageNumber="35" rank="species" species="extrema">
<emphasis box="[649,772,1774,1799]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="35">S. extrema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on one single female specimen from Tenasserim, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,235,1813,1839]" name="Myanmar" pageId="6" pageNumber="35">Burma</collectingCountry>
. We were not able to see any specimens of this species. This species can be distinguished from other species in the genus by the vertex with three black spots at apex with the median one longish, and the fore wings with the two middle anteapical cells equally long and with 
<number box="[946,975,1892,1918]" pageId="6" pageNumber="35" value="16.0">16</number>
apical cells and 
<number box="[1181,1196,1892,1918]" pageId="6" pageNumber="35" value="7.0">7</number>
subapical cells (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Melichar" box="[151,333,1932,1958]" pageId="6" pageNumber="44" refString="Melichar, L. (1914) Monographie der Tropiduchinen (Homoptera). Verhandlungen des Naturforschenden Vereins in Brunn, 53, 1 - 145." type="journal article" year="1914">
Melichar, 
<number box="[270,333,1932,1958]" pageId="6" pageNumber="35" value="1914.0">1914</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1374,2037]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1436,152,538]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="36" pageId="6" pageNumber="35">
It is necessary to make a note on the distribution of 
<taxonomicName box="[827,952,1972,1997]" genus="Logana" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="6" pageNumber="35" rank="species" species="extrema">
<emphasis box="[827,952,1972,1997]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="35">S. extrema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In Metcalf’s (
<number box="[1133,1194,1971,1997]" pageId="6" pageNumber="35" value="1954.0">1954</number>
) catalogue of world 
<taxonomicName authority="Chekiang" authorityName="Chekiang" box="[151,449,2011,2037]" class="Insecta" family="Tropiduchidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Tropiduchidae, Chekiang</taxonomicName>
[Zhejiang], 
<collectingCountry box="[597,667,2011,2037]" name="China" pageId="6" pageNumber="35">China</collectingCountry>
is listed as one distribution record of this species. However, this record, judged from Lallemand’s (
<number box="[552,613,152,178]" pageId="7" pageNumber="36" value="1942.0">1942</number>
) paper by 
<bibRefCitation author="Metcalf" box="[738,917,152,178]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" refString="Metcalf, Z. P. (1954) General Catalogue of the Homoptera. Fasc. IV. Fulgoroidea. Part 11. Tropiduchidae. North Carolina State College, Raleigh, NC, USA. 167 pp." type="book" year="1954">
Metcalf (
<number box="[845,908,152,178]" pageId="7" pageNumber="36" value="1954.0">1954</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, is questionable. 
<bibRefCitation author="Lallemand" box="[1119,1329,152,178]" pageId="7" pageNumber="43" refString="Lallemand, H. (1942). Notes sur quelques especes recueillies par le R. P. Piel (Musee Heude Shanghai) et le R. P. De Cooman (Hoa Binh, Tonkin). Notes d'entomologie Chinoise, 9, 69 - 77." type="journal article" year="1942">
Lallemand (
<number box="[1260,1321,152,178]" pageId="7" pageNumber="36" value="1942.0">1942</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
received some materials, sent by R. P. De Cooman, collected in Hoa Binh (northern 
<collectingCountry box="[1026,1127,192,218]" name="Vietnam" pageId="7" pageNumber="36">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
) and just after, specimens, sent by R. P. Piel, some collected in Hoa Binh and others in the Mountains of T’ienmu-shan (prov. Chekiang, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,226,272,298]" name="China" pageId="7" pageNumber="36">China</collectingCountry>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Lallemand" box="[246,457,272,298]" pageId="7" pageNumber="43" refString="Lallemand, H. (1942). Notes sur quelques especes recueillies par le R. P. Piel (Musee Heude Shanghai) et le R. P. De Cooman (Hoa Binh, Tonkin). Notes d'entomologie Chinoise, 9, 69 - 77." type="journal article" year="1942">
Lallemand (
<number box="[388,449,272,298]" pageId="7" pageNumber="36" value="1942.0">1942</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
just provided a list of the species he identified but he did not give any information on the specimens he examined and the distribution data of the species. It is not possible to determine if the specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[312,434,352,377]" genus="Logana" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="7" pageNumber="36" rank="species" species="extrema">
<emphasis box="[312,434,352,377]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="36">S. extrema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
identified by Lallemand come from Hoa Binh in northern 
<collectingCountry box="[1121,1220,352,378]" name="Vietnam" pageId="7" pageNumber="36">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
or from Chekiang in southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[335,409,392,418]" name="China" pageId="7" pageNumber="36">China</collectingCountry>
. A re-examination of the Lallemand’s (
<number box="[872,933,392,418]" pageId="7" pageNumber="36" value="1942.0">1942</number>
) specimens is needed. Lallemand’s (
<number box="[1366,1427,392,418]" pageId="7" pageNumber="36" value="1942.0">1942</number>
) identification of 
<taxonomicName authority="Melichar" authorityName="Melichar" box="[346,582,432,458]" genus="Logana" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="7" pageNumber="36" rank="species" species="extrema">
<emphasis box="[346,468,432,457]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="36">S. extrema</emphasis>
Melichar
</taxonomicName>
also needs to be checked.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,152,538]" pageId="7" pageNumber="36">
It is interesting to note that in Lallemand’s (
<number box="[734,795,472,498]" pageId="7" pageNumber="36" value="1942.0">1942</number>
) paper the identified species was wrongly spelled as 
<taxonomicName box="[151,341,512,537]" genus="Logana" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="7" pageNumber="36" rank="species" species="extrema">
<emphasis box="[151,341,512,537]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="36">Logana extrema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
UHL.
</paragraph>
